@startuml uc-06-statediagram
title UC06 — Vocabulary tests/activities by selected level/topic — State Diagram
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FEFEFE
  BorderColor #333333
  FontName Helvetica
}

[*] --> NotStarted
NotStarted --> LoadingContext : open topic test/activity

LoadingContext --> LatestContentReady : active level/topic content found
LoadingContext --> CachedContentReady : new crawl not ready/fails
LoadingContext --> NoContentAvailable : no active/cached content

LatestContentReady --> ActivityReady : build tasks from active content
CachedContentReady --> ActivityReady : build tasks from cached content
NoContentAvailable --> [*] : show empty state

state "Activity In Progress" as InProgress {
  [*] --> FlashcardTask
  FlashcardTask --> MultipleChoiceTask : next item
  MultipleChoiceTask --> FillBlankTask : next item
  FillBlankTask --> GrammarMappingTask : next item
  GrammarMappingTask --> ReviewAnswers : review
  ReviewAnswers --> [*]
}

ActivityReady --> InProgress : start tasks
InProgress --> PendingRequiredAnswers : submit with missing answers
PendingRequiredAnswers --> InProgress : complete missing answers
InProgress --> Evaluating : submit completed attempt
Evaluating --> Scored : correct / total x 100%
Scored --> Saved : persist attempt and answers
Saved --> Completed : result displayed
Completed --> [*]

InProgress --> Cancelled : exit activity
Cancelled --> [*]

LatestContentReady --> RefreshedForNewAttempt : weekly sync published update
RefreshedForNewAttempt --> ActivityReady : use latest active content

note right of CachedContentReady
  Uses current cached active content
  when latest Langeek crawl output is
  unavailable or not yet published.
end note

note bottom of Saved
  Saved results keep user, selected level,
  topic, question IDs, content version,
  and score. Later content sync does not
  modify previous attempt results.
end note
@enduml
